To enter the building security have to buzz you in. At certain times you will need student or staff ID to enter the building.

Visitors - you should report to security at the door to notify them.

name: Maybeck High School
directions: Enter from Garber street or the door on the patio by the railing that overlooks the parking lot, and it's right up the stairs across from the main office. If you enter from near where the Saint John's Church office is, you can go up the stairs (or take the elevator if you have mobility issues) and it's at the other end of the hall.
comment:
The school is open campus and shares a building with Saint John's Church, so a stranger using the bathroom isn't in the least suspicious. It's an extremely small school and certain of the teachers and students are abnormally friendly, so people will recognize if you're lost and give you directions, unsolicited advice about applying to the school, an off-key rendition of Katy Perry's "Firework," or sometimes sliced pineapple. 

The multi-stall gender neutral restroom is open whenever the high school or the church is, so at least Sunday-Monday, sometimes more. It closes in the late afternoons, usually around 5:00. The first stall is a urinal.
